 :freeware: n. Free software, often written by enthusiasts and distributed by
users' groups, or via electronic mail, local bulletin boards, {Usenet}, or
other electronic media. At one time, `freeware' was a trademark of Andrew
Fluegelman, the author of the well-known MS-DOS comm program PC-TALK III. It
wasn't enforced after his mysterious disappearance and presumed death in
1984. see {shareware}, {FRS}.